snippet.textDisplay: I've watched this fight 7 times...watched every punch...I don't understand anyone who says this was a 'boring' fight...I was on the edge of my seat for 12 rounds until Andy beckoned AJ in the last 20 seconds when I knew it was done...Watching a fight knowing that one punch can change the fight in a second is so thrilling to watch live...Its almost as if the 'boring' naysayers have only watched boxing highlights on youtube and then expect a live fight to be the same...Modern culture I guess...I watched Ali, Norton, Foreman, Ray Leonard, Hagler, Hearns,  live in the 70's as a kid...This story was just as good...I thank all boxers, coaches and promoters past and present for making this sport the most exciting and thoroughly entertaining past time for me in my armchair!

snippet.textDisplay:
First congrats to AJ for the win, his spirit and bahaviour in and out of the ring.AJ brought a very good point: Andy all he did in most of the fight, both is try to hit around the face and behind the head, which to me is cheating. To me this is cheating and I am surprised nothing much was said about that.As AJ said, I don't think a fighter is not trained to get hit there, which is why he didn;t recover the first knock out.


If someone does not believe it, please take a look at many of the punches of Andy in both fights. I think he did it on purpose.


No doubt that the fighter has always a different perspective of the fight to someone that is just watching.


I think he is very smart and carisma to be one of the greatest of all time.
